About dataset This dataset is having data of customers who buys clothes online. The store offers in-store style and clothing advice sessions. Customers come in to the store, have sessions/meetings with a personal stylist, then they can go home and order either on a mobile app or website for the clothes they want.

Introduction

This Dataset consist of customer amount spent on online shopping of clothes.The company is trying to decide whether to focus their efforts on their mobile app experience or their website.Firstly we are going to loading and understand the data. Lets Start

#Handling Outliers
Q1 = df.quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df.quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1

df = df[~((df< (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR)) |(df > (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR))).any(axis=1)]

#Extracting X and Y from dataset
x=df.iloc[:,[1,2]].values
y=df.iloc[:,-1].values
In [20]:
#Splitting training and test dataset
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
x_train,x_test,y_train,y_test=train_test_split(x,y,test_size=0.3)

#WHAT SHOULD THE ECOMMERCE DO?
From the above finding we can come to conculsion that more customer tend to buy from Mobile App rather than using website
Suggestion to company 
1.Since they are many customer using Mobile App concentrate more on app development and speed.
2.Since website is not performing good we can do some A/B experiment and upgrade the website for more sales in future.
